  "Trainers and SMEs Sourcing": "培训师与 SME 寻聘",
  "A community of practitioners, on call.": "一支随时待命的从业者社群。",
  "The toughest part of most curriculum development is finding the subject-matter expert. We keep a working community of practitioners across the sectors in which we currently practise, pair them to the engagement at no cost to the training provider, and warmly invite trainers and subject-matter experts in other sectors to work with us.": "大多数课程开发中最棘手的部分，是找到合适的领域专家。我们在目前从事实践的各行业中维持着一支务实的从业者社群，将他们与项目配对而不向培训机构收取任何费用，并诚挚邀请其他行业的培训师与领域专家与我们合作。",
  "An arch holds quietly because every stone is set in its right place. A community of practitioners works the same way, matched to the engagement, no more, no less.": "拱门得以静静屹立，是因为每一块石头都安放在正确的位置。从业者社群亦是如此运作——与项目恰当配对，不多，亦不少。",
  "The shape of a community · still life · restraint as a working principle.": "社群的形态 · 静物 · 以克制为行事之本。",
  "SSG's Skills Demand for the Future Economy report organises Singapore's sectoral demand around three priority economies. Our community currently practises within parts of each, and grows by invitation rather than by overreach.": "SSG 的《未来经济技能需求》报告将新加坡的行业需求归纳为三大优先经济。我们的社群目前在其中各部分从事实践，并以邀请而非过度扩张的方式成长。",
  "Curriculum rarely fails for want of a writer. It fails for want of the one person who has actually done the work, and finding that person is the real engagement.": "课程鲜少因缺少撰写者而失败，而是因缺少那位真正做过这项工作的人而失败——找到那个人，才是真正的工程。",
  "From the practice · Sourcing": "源自本所实践 · 寻聘",
  "In demand courses": "热门需求课程",
  "§ III · The pairing": "§ III · 配对",
  "Paired to your engagement, at no cost to you, and none to the learner.": "与您的项目配对，您无须付费，学员亦无须付费。",
  "The toughest part of most curriculum development is the subject-matter expert. Without one, the Course Proposal Form cannot be submitted; with the wrong one, the courseware will not survive the Course Quality Check. We keep a working community, prepared and ready, drawn from practitioners who have committed time to the community on the same understanding that we have: that good training ought not to be priced out of reach.": "大多数课程开发中最棘手的部分，便是领域专家。没有领域专家，《课程建议书》便无法提交；找错了人，课程教材则无法通过课程质量检查。我们维持着一支务实、随时待命的社群，成员来自那些以与我们相同的理念投入时间于社群的从业者：好的培训不应被定价至遥不可及。",
  "Where your engagement can be matched from our community, the pairing is free. We do not levy a finder's fee, a placement margin or a per-hour markup on top of the SME's own rate. Where our practitioners cannot match the engagement, we source through the usual recruitment channels (Jobstreet and the like) and recover only the direct costs of the search and administrative costs.": "凡您的项目能从我们社群中匹配时，配对均为免费。我们不会在 SME 自身费率之上加收介绍费、安置差价或按小时的加价。若我们的从业者无法匹配该项目，我们将通过常规招聘渠道（如 Jobstreet 等）寻聘，并仅收回搜寻的直接成本与行政成本。",
  "A short note on what we are not: 2birds is not a recruitment agency. We do not hold a recruitment licence and we do not place candidates into employment. We make introductions; we do not negotiate contracts on anyone's behalf.": "关于我们并非什么，谨作简短说明：2birds 并非招聘中介。我们不持有招聘牌照，也不为候选人安排就业。我们只作引荐；我们不代表任何一方协商合同。",
  "An invitation": "一份邀请",
  "If you are a certified adult educator or a subject-matter expert with standing in your sector, write to us. Our community is open by invitation, and we are always glad to be in correspondence with practitioners we have not yet met.": "若您是经认证的成人教育工作者，或在所属行业中享有声望的领域专家，请来信予我们。我们的社群以邀请方式开放，而我们始终乐于与尚未谋面的从业者书信往来。",
  "– A standing invitation to the practice": "— 一份对本所敞开的长期邀请",
